ce:section.ce:para:
Nanozymes designed based on the research have a variety of enzyme activities and different dimensional structures, which can be widely combined with enzyme characteristics and applied in the field of analytical sensing [157]. So far, many nanozymes have been successfully developed into colorimetric sensors, electrochemical sensors, or combined enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) methods to detect food additives, disease markers, metal ions, tumor cell microenvironment, pathogen detection, and so on can also be used as antibacterial materials (Fig. 7
                     ). In this section, the recent advances of nanozymes applied for sensing disease, tumor microenvironment (TME), pathogen, drug, food, and environment have been reviewed (Table 1
                     ).
